WEBVTT

00:04.305 --> 00:04.772
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:28.529 --> 00:30.798
Bill overdue, final notice,
noise complaint,

00:30.831 --> 00:32.800
traffic violation,
cease and desist,

00:32.833 --> 00:34.502
restraining order...

00:34.535 --> 00:36.670
Dad, what are we supposed to do
with all this?
Well...

00:36.704 --> 00:39.307
paper can be used
in many creative ways

00:39.340 --> 00:42.243
and turned into
a lot of interesting things,

00:42.276 --> 00:43.377
like a duck...

00:43.411 --> 00:44.445
or fashion...

00:44.478 --> 00:45.546
inventions...

00:45.579 --> 00:47.215
and other...things.

00:47.248 --> 00:48.616
Come on!

00:48.649 --> 00:50.017
There's got to be
at least one good letter!

00:50.050 --> 00:52.186
Actually, yeah.
We've got an invitation.

00:52.220 --> 00:54.422
Huh?
We've never had
one of those before.

00:54.455 --> 00:55.656
That's not true.

00:55.689 --> 00:57.891
I've been invited to court
several times.

00:58.692 --> 01:00.294
No, it's from
the mayor.

01:00.328 --> 01:02.830
He wants us to go to
the town hall for a surprise?

01:02.863 --> 01:04.698
Maybe they'll reveal
a statue of me.

01:04.732 --> 01:07.034
Why would they be making
a statue of you?

01:07.067 --> 01:08.102
I sit a lot,

01:08.136 --> 01:09.737
which makes me
a pretty reliable life model.

01:09.770 --> 01:11.472
And I'm a great example
to people.

01:11.505 --> 01:14.175
They're more likely to make
some kind of example of you.

01:14.208 --> 01:16.177
Maybe they've cleared up
that legal grey area

01:16.210 --> 01:18.712
about whether I'm a feral animal
or your child.

01:18.746 --> 01:21.715
Mom: Oh, honey, you're the same
as all my kids --

01:21.749 --> 01:23.016
a combination
of both.

01:23.050 --> 01:25.486
I guess we'll just
have to go and find out.

01:25.519 --> 01:27.188
All:
Go, Wattersons, go!

01:27.221 --> 01:28.656
Go, Wattersons, go!

01:28.689 --> 01:30.057
I don't want to say
I told you so,

01:30.090 --> 01:32.393
because I won't be heard
over all of this cheering --

01:32.426 --> 01:33.661
so I'll
shout it instead.

01:33.694 --> 01:35.663
I told you so!

01:35.696 --> 01:36.897
[ Laughing ] Welcome!

01:36.930 --> 01:38.899
Our Social Services
have decided

01:38.932 --> 01:40.634
to offer you
a new house!

01:40.668 --> 01:42.136
[ Cheering ]
Impossible.

01:42.170 --> 01:44.805
What's the catch?
There's always a catch.

01:44.838 --> 01:46.640
There's only a few
Compulsory Additional Terms,

01:46.674 --> 01:47.908
Conditions,
and Hypothecations --

01:47.941 --> 01:49.477
or C.A.T.C.H.es
for short!

01:49.510 --> 01:50.644
What do you mean?

01:50.678 --> 01:52.180
Well,
the people of Elmore

01:52.213 --> 01:54.148
thought you deserved a brand-new
house in a brand-new state

01:54.182 --> 01:56.217
with brand-new neighbors
who can put up with you,

01:56.250 --> 01:58.018
a brand-new police force
to deal with you,

01:58.051 --> 02:00.821
and a brand-new court system
to prosecute you.

02:00.854 --> 02:03.457
That sounds more like
a punishment than a reward.

02:03.491 --> 02:04.792
No one said
it was a reward.

02:04.825 --> 02:06.460
They said
it's what you deserve.

02:06.494 --> 02:07.895
But that's like
banishing us!

02:07.928 --> 02:09.963
Think of it more like
witness protection.

02:09.997 --> 02:12.833
We're just protecting people
from witnessing you ever again!

02:12.866 --> 02:15.936
All: Go, Wattersons, go!
Go, Wattersons, go!

02:15.969 --> 02:19.072
Kind of feels less encouraging
when you can see their faces.

02:19.106 --> 02:20.841
Anais: They want us
to move to Ohio?!

02:20.874 --> 02:22.476
The home state of eight people
who became president

02:22.510 --> 02:24.245
just so they didn't have to
stay living there?!

02:24.278 --> 02:26.947
I never realized
our neighbors hated us so much.

02:26.980 --> 02:29.217
A few rotten tomatoes
in the face, sure,

02:29.250 --> 02:32.220
a few "No Dogs or Wattersons"
signs in store windows,

02:32.253 --> 02:33.387
fair enough.

02:33.421 --> 02:34.988
The occasional
light-hearted arson attack,

02:35.022 --> 02:36.957
harsh, but fair.
But get rid of us?!

02:36.990 --> 02:39.460
Let's be honest --
we're the only family in town

02:39.493 --> 02:40.794
to have somehow
committed a crime

02:40.828 --> 02:42.630
in every category
of misdemeanor.

02:42.663 --> 02:44.432
Go, Wattersons!

02:44.465 --> 02:45.833
It's not
a good thing, Dad!

02:45.866 --> 02:48.035
If you're going to do
something wrong, do it right!

02:48.068 --> 02:49.670
Just look
at this crime map.

02:49.703 --> 02:52.306
All of this is us.
Public nudity...

02:53.140 --> 02:55.243
[ Screams ]
[ Gasps ]

02:55.276 --> 02:56.510
[ Screaming continues ]

02:56.544 --> 02:58.879
Ah! Ah! Ah!
Ah! Ah! Ah!

02:58.912 --> 03:02.383
Ah! Ah! Ah!
[ Screams ]

03:02.416 --> 03:04.618
Anais:
...wasting 911 resources...
[ Telephone rings ]

03:04.652 --> 03:06.153
911 dispatch,
how can I help?

03:06.186 --> 03:08.789
Darwin: I've got a pain
in my chest. It's my heart!

03:08.822 --> 03:11.024
Oh, for the last time, kid,
being heartbroken

03:11.058 --> 03:13.827
because elephants can't jump
is not a medical emergency.

03:13.861 --> 03:15.663
[ Dial tone ]

03:15.696 --> 03:17.665
...parking violations...
[ Gasps ]

03:17.698 --> 03:21.101
[ Tires screech ]

03:21.134 --> 03:23.203
[ Whistling ]

03:23.237 --> 03:25.105
[ Growls ]

03:26.139 --> 03:28.476
Hmm? [ Gasps ]

03:28.509 --> 03:29.677
♪♪

03:29.710 --> 03:31.345
Anais: ...vandalism...

03:31.379 --> 03:35.249
[ Whistling ]

03:38.619 --> 03:40.621
Hmm...a bit obvious,
don't you think?

03:40.654 --> 03:42.656
The hand-crafted,
effortful creation

03:42.690 --> 03:44.124
of each individual
porcelain seed

03:44.157 --> 03:45.826
queries the modern phenomena
of mass production

03:45.859 --> 03:47.227
and replication.

03:47.261 --> 03:48.496
Am I right?

03:48.529 --> 03:51.265
♪♪

03:51.299 --> 03:52.500
You're right.

03:52.533 --> 03:54.335
If only people
would get to know the real us.

03:54.368 --> 03:55.536
[ Clears throat ]

03:55.569 --> 03:57.938
[ Sniffs ]

03:57.971 --> 04:00.708
Ha! Take that, science!

04:00.741 --> 04:02.142
[ Screams ]

04:02.175 --> 04:03.977
I don't think Mom meant
the real, real us, obviously.

04:04.011 --> 04:06.447
More like the Elmogram
super-filtered avatar

04:06.480 --> 04:07.615
hat requires 45 takes

04:07.648 --> 04:09.483
to get it
as flattering as possible.

04:09.517 --> 04:11.218
So, our fake selves,
then?

04:11.251 --> 04:12.420
Yes.

04:12.453 --> 04:14.187
If people could only
get to know the fake-real us.

04:14.221 --> 04:16.557
Let's show our neighbors
how nice we are

04:16.590 --> 04:19.059
when we're not
being ourselves.

04:19.092 --> 04:21.962
Thank you for your help,
but please be careful.

04:21.995 --> 04:24.365
If I get a good price
for this cabinet,

04:24.398 --> 04:26.934
it's hello
two-week luxury cruise!

04:26.967 --> 04:28.736
Don't worry, Marvin!
I'm sure your cabinet

04:28.769 --> 04:31.071
will have
a great vacation.
Okay, Dad!

04:31.104 --> 04:33.507
Gumball: Are you ready
on your end?
Got it!

04:33.541 --> 04:34.742
Here it comes!

04:34.775 --> 04:37.345
♪♪

04:37.378 --> 04:38.579
[ Sighs ]

04:38.612 --> 04:40.381
That was a long detour,
but at least that man

04:40.414 --> 04:43.917
got to see his grandmother
one last time in Nebraska.

04:43.951 --> 04:47.355
Wait.
Didn't he say Nevada?

04:47.388 --> 04:49.623
[ Tires screech ]

04:49.657 --> 04:50.924
[ Groaning ]

04:50.958 --> 04:52.326
[ Sighs ]
[ Door creaks ]

04:52.360 --> 04:53.527
Hmm?

04:53.561 --> 04:55.929
♪♪

04:57.398 --> 04:58.899
[ Door creaks ]

04:58.932 --> 05:02.135
Who said, "The object of art
is to give life a shape"?

05:02.169 --> 05:03.337
Uh...

05:03.371 --> 05:04.605
Psst!

05:04.638 --> 05:06.139
[ Gasps ]

05:06.173 --> 05:07.575
♪♪

05:07.608 --> 05:10.378
That's right,
Shakespeare -- Oh.

05:10.411 --> 05:13.146
Hmm.
Hmm.

05:13.180 --> 05:15.683
[ Crickets chirping ]
[ Chuckles ]

05:15.716 --> 05:17.418
[ Grunts ]

05:17.451 --> 05:18.686
[ Gasps ]

05:18.719 --> 05:20.521
Here, take it.

05:20.554 --> 05:21.755
Okay.

05:22.623 --> 05:25.626
[ Gasps ]
It came with
a two-year warranty.

05:25.659 --> 05:27.260
Okay.

05:27.294 --> 05:29.830
How about a hug
before you go?

05:29.863 --> 05:31.832
Not okay.

05:31.865 --> 05:34.935
Announcer:
Local man saves pet cobra
from snake charmer's flute.

05:34.968 --> 05:38.872
Local boy stops school bullying
by making himself sole target.

05:38.906 --> 05:40.508
His secret -- sock suspenders.

05:40.541 --> 05:43.143
Local girl brings metric system
to Elmore,

05:43.176 --> 05:45.479
puts end to people measuring
things with their feet.

05:45.513 --> 05:48.616
"Watterson family -- not as bad
as we thought," says person.

05:48.649 --> 05:51.151
"I agree with that person,"
says another person.

05:51.184 --> 05:52.886
Elmore Times editor fired

05:52.920 --> 05:55.456
for obsessive coverage
of local family.

05:55.489 --> 05:58.158
It worked, Mother!
Our efforts succeeded!

05:58.191 --> 05:59.993
Everyone in the town
loves us.

06:00.027 --> 06:02.763
[ Laughter ]

06:02.796 --> 06:06.066
[ All grunting ]

06:06.099 --> 06:07.267
[ "Kumbaya" playing ]
[ Glass shatters ]

06:07.300 --> 06:09.503
What is happening
to us?!

06:09.537 --> 06:10.838
[ Groaning ]

06:10.871 --> 06:12.506
[ Screaming ]

06:12.540 --> 06:14.708
We went too far!

06:14.742 --> 06:16.977
We're becoming...

06:17.010 --> 06:19.379
model citizens!

06:19.413 --> 06:23.617
[ Screaming ]
My leg! My leg!

06:23.651 --> 06:25.419
[ Groaning ]

06:25.453 --> 06:27.154
[ Howling ]

06:27.187 --> 06:28.556
My face!

06:28.589 --> 06:29.757
[ Screaming ]

06:29.790 --> 06:30.958
[ Ding! ]

06:30.991 --> 06:32.626
[ Panting ]

06:32.660 --> 06:33.961
[ Ding! ]

06:33.994 --> 06:37.531
[ Music continues ]

06:38.999 --> 06:41.168
[ Telephone rings ]

06:42.035 --> 06:43.336
Howdy-doody you do?

06:43.370 --> 06:44.905
[ Man speaking indistinctly ]

06:44.938 --> 06:46.306
Absolutamundo, sir.

06:46.339 --> 06:48.341
We'll be with you
in two shakes of a widdle-dee!

06:48.375 --> 06:51.378
Zoopity-boopity, bye!
What was that?

06:51.411 --> 06:52.646
I have no idea.

06:52.680 --> 06:55.015
It's like I just washed
my mouth out with a choir boy

06:55.048 --> 06:56.917
and now it's coming out
in dweeb speak.

06:56.950 --> 06:58.886
Not that,
who was on the phone?

06:58.919 --> 07:00.220
Oh, the Mayor.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.989
He wants us to skippity-hop
over to his office.

07:02.022 --> 07:03.657
♪♪

07:03.691 --> 07:05.459
I misjudged you,
Wattersons.

07:05.493 --> 07:08.295
So you don't want us
to leave anymore?

07:08.328 --> 07:10.664
No! I want you
in my gated community.

07:10.698 --> 07:12.766
Is that some kind of euphemism
for prison?

07:12.800 --> 07:14.201
[ Laughs ]

07:14.234 --> 07:16.136
Yes, but all the criminals
are on the outside.

07:16.169 --> 07:18.739
Everyone wanted you gone
because you were, well...

07:18.772 --> 07:19.940
being you.

07:19.973 --> 07:21.642
Whereas I wanted you out

07:21.675 --> 07:23.777
because you were bringing the
price of the neighborhood down.

07:23.811 --> 07:25.178
That was a problem, you see,

07:25.212 --> 07:27.047
when I decided to sell the land
to developers.

07:27.080 --> 07:28.315
But look at you now --

07:28.348 --> 07:30.083
you've become
our new poster family.

07:30.117 --> 07:31.952
But what about
the other neighbors?

07:31.985 --> 07:33.420
The bank owns their houses.

07:33.453 --> 07:35.656
We just have to make it
difficult for them to pay.

07:35.689 --> 07:37.190
But what'll happen
to them?

07:37.224 --> 07:38.859
Should that worry you?

07:38.892 --> 07:41.662
Well, they didn't really care
what was going to happen to you.

07:41.695 --> 07:42.896
What if we say no?

07:42.930 --> 07:45.666
You can't say no
to progress.

07:45.699 --> 07:47.234
[ All sigh ]

07:48.301 --> 07:49.837
What are we gonna do?

07:49.870 --> 07:51.304
I guess either way,
we lose.

07:51.338 --> 07:52.305
Dad: No!

07:52.339 --> 07:54.675
The people of Elmore
might be haters,

07:54.708 --> 07:55.976
but they're our haters!

07:56.009 --> 07:58.178
They're like
an old pair of underwear --

07:58.211 --> 08:00.380
sure,
there's not much support there,

08:00.413 --> 08:03.383
and sure, they sometimes
leave us hanging in the wind,

08:03.416 --> 08:05.753
but they're something
we're familiar with!

08:05.786 --> 08:09.256
And I, for one, will not have
some big corporation

08:09.289 --> 08:11.925
forcing me
to change my underwear!

08:11.959 --> 08:13.393
Yeah! Yeah!
Yeah! Yeah!

08:13.426 --> 08:14.461
But also, ugh!

08:14.494 --> 08:16.830
That still
doesn't answer my question.

08:16.864 --> 08:18.165
What are we gonna do?

08:18.198 --> 08:19.700
Okay, this is all about
house prices, right?

08:19.733 --> 08:21.835
If we pulled them up once,
we can pull them back down.

08:21.869 --> 08:23.203
Dad:
Like a pair of old--

08:23.236 --> 08:25.639
The underwear thing
had its moment, honey.

08:25.673 --> 08:27.007
But Anais is right.

08:27.040 --> 08:29.777
It's like they say --
if you truly love something,

08:29.810 --> 08:32.445
make it look as ugly as possible
to everyone else

08:32.479 --> 08:35.616
so it'll have no choice
but to stay with you.

08:35.649 --> 08:39.620
[ Rock music plays ]

08:39.653 --> 08:42.522
[ Screaming ]

08:42.556 --> 08:43.757
Is it me,

08:43.791 --> 08:46.126
or are these termites
a little more hectic than usual?

08:46.159 --> 08:47.895
[ Panting ]

08:47.928 --> 08:49.496
[ Roars ]

08:49.529 --> 08:50.631
[ Screaming ]

08:50.664 --> 08:52.432
Hmm. That might be
all the bath salts

08:52.465 --> 08:54.301
I've been pouring
into the water supply.

08:54.334 --> 08:56.169
[ Music continues ]

08:57.638 --> 08:58.939
[ Doorbell rings ]

08:58.972 --> 09:00.841
What is
going on here?

09:00.874 --> 09:02.309
Hmm.

09:03.143 --> 09:04.511
Nothing here.

09:04.544 --> 09:05.746
Eh, never mind.

09:05.779 --> 09:07.480
[ Music continues ]

09:07.514 --> 09:10.684
You know what the biggest sign
of a bad neighborhood is?

09:10.718 --> 09:12.019
Broken windows.

09:12.052 --> 09:13.220
[ Grunts ]

09:13.253 --> 09:15.623
Ow!
[ Groans, grunts ]

09:15.656 --> 09:16.824
Ow!

09:16.857 --> 09:19.459
[ Grunts ]

09:19.492 --> 09:22.029
You know what the biggest sign
of a bad neighborhood is?

09:22.062 --> 09:23.263
Boarded-up windows.

09:23.296 --> 09:24.798
I thought you said
you--

09:24.832 --> 09:26.900
[ Screams ]
[ Groans ]

09:26.934 --> 09:29.670
[ Music continues ]

09:37.010 --> 09:38.779
[ Whistling ]

09:38.812 --> 09:41.348
[ Music continues ]

09:47.855 --> 09:50.457
We do this the easy way
and nobody gets hurt.

09:50.490 --> 09:52.225
Okay,
whatever you say, man!

09:52.259 --> 09:53.460
Just be cool,
be cool!

09:53.493 --> 09:55.062
You know what I want,
right?

09:55.095 --> 09:56.396
Yeah,
no problem!

09:56.429 --> 09:58.498
Eh?
No, you goof!

09:58.531 --> 09:59.700
I want you
to take this bat

09:59.733 --> 10:01.301
and go mug people
in the neighborhood!

10:01.334 --> 10:03.837
[ Music continues ]

10:03.871 --> 10:06.674
[ Grunts ]
[ Laughs ]

10:06.707 --> 10:08.208
[ Groans ]

10:09.076 --> 10:10.944
[ Match striking ]

10:10.978 --> 10:13.180
This is for you,
Elmore.

10:13.213 --> 10:16.650
[ Music continues ]

10:17.651 --> 10:20.153
[ Dogs barking, alarms blaring ]
Mayor: Oh, good job!

10:20.187 --> 10:22.055
There's no point
in selling the land anymore.

10:22.089 --> 10:23.724
You scared away
the rich people!

10:23.757 --> 10:25.826
Bet you guys feel really big,
don't you?

10:25.859 --> 10:28.295
Picking on the poor,
defenseless billionaires.

10:28.328 --> 10:30.097
Elmore is not
for sale!

10:30.130 --> 10:31.298
Oh, I see.

10:31.331 --> 10:32.800
You mean the lesson in all this

10:32.833 --> 10:34.634
is that some things
are more valuable than money.

10:34.668 --> 10:36.536
Exactly.

10:36.569 --> 10:40.107
[ Laughs ]
What would that even be?!

10:40.140 --> 10:42.475
Laugh if you wish.
[ Laughing continues ]

10:42.509 --> 10:44.978
All right,
that's enough.
[ Laughing continues ]

10:45.012 --> 10:47.380
Okay,
you can stop now.
[ Laughing continues ]

10:47.414 --> 10:48.782
Fine!

10:48.816 --> 10:50.117
Laugh all you want.

10:50.150 --> 10:52.920
But the decent, honest people
of this town

10:52.953 --> 10:56.990
will thank us for
everything we did to save them.

10:57.024 --> 10:58.959
All:
Go, Wattersons, go!

10:58.992 --> 11:00.393
Go, Wattersons, go!
Hmm.

11:04.832 --> 11:05.298
[ Theme music plays ]
